  startText: {fileID: 0}
  mediumPromptTextContent: 'The following C++ code is supposed to increment the original
    value, but it does not.

    Fix the bug.'
  mediumPromptText: {fileID: 0}
  mediumPromptFadeDuration: 0.32
  mediumPromptTypeDelay: 0.018
  mediumCssInitialCode: "#include <iostream>\n\nvoid increment(int n) {\n    n++;\n}\n\nint
    main() {\n    int value = 5;\n    increment(value);\n    std::cout << value <<
    std::endl;\n}"
  mediumCssCorrectCode: "#include <iostream>\n\nvoid increment(int& n) {\n    n++;\n}\n\nint
    main() {\n    int value = 5;\n    increment(value);\n    std::cout << value <<
    std::endl;\n}"
  mediumCodePanel: {fileID: 0}
  mediumCodeInputField: {fileID: 0}
  mediumVerifyButton: {fileID: 0}
  mediumVerifyResultText: {fileID: 0}
  mediumLeaveButton: {fileID: 0}
  mediumContinueButton: {fileID: 0}
  mediumHintButton: {fileID: 0}
  mediumTutorialPanel: {fileID: 0}
  mediumTutorialTitleText: {fileID: 0}
  mediumTutorialBodyText: {fileID: 0}
  mediumBackToQuestionButton: {fileID: 0}
  mediumTutorialContent: "Step by step:\n1) `increment(int n)` receives a copy, not
    the original variable.\n2) Incrementing `n` changes only the local copy.\n3)
    Use `int& n` to modify the caller's value.\n\nCorrect answer:\n#include <iostream>\n\nvoid
    increment(int& n) {\n    n++;\n}\n\nint main() {\n    int value = 5;\n    increment(value);\n   
    std::cout << value << std::endl;\n}"
